{%- comment -%}
  ============================================================================
  SP PACK REGISTRY — single source of truth for pack vertical identity
  ============================================================================

  This is the ONLY file in the theme that maps a template suffix to a vertical
  identity and its vertical content (brand name, product handle, CSS classes,
  browser titles, fallback assets, etc.).

  Core theme files (layout/theme.liquid, sections/*.liquid, snippets/cart-*.liquid)
  MUST NOT reference "supplement", "Daily Vitality", vertical product handles, or
  any other vertical-specific string directly. They ask this registry instead.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  USAGE
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Scalar lookup (returns a string, or blank when not applicable):

    {%- capture sp_brand -%}
      {%- render 'sp-pack-registry', field: 'brand_name' -%}
    {%- endcapture -%}

  Optional explicit vertical (defaults to the active template suffix):

    {%- render 'sp-pack-registry', field: 'brand_name', vertical: 'supplement' -%}

  IMPORTANT — Dispatching to snippets by variable name:
  Shopify Liquid silently no-ops a `render variableName` call when the variable
  contains a snippet name (dynamic render). This is a known Liquid limitation.
  Any consumer that needs to conditionally render a snippet based on the active
  vertical MUST use a static `case` statement keyed on the `active` field:

    {%- capture sp_vertical_active -%}{%- render 'sp-pack-registry', field: 'active' -%}{%- endcapture -%}
    {%- case sp_vertical_active -%}
      {%- when 'supplement' -%}{%- render 'sp-supplement-head' -%}
    {%- endcase -%}

  String values returned by the registry (brand_name, product_handle, etc.) work
  fine as captured variables used in `if` conditions, output, or Liquid expressions.

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  FIELDS
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    active                 → vertical id (e.g. 'supplement') or blank
    html_class             → classes to add to <html> (no leading space)
    brand_name             → vertical brand/store name
    product_handle         → primary vertical product handle
    title_index            → <title> for the homepage
    title_cart             → <title> for the cart page
    title_product_suffix   → string appended after product.title in <title>
    footer_hidden_links    → comma list of footer link labels to hide (lowercase)
    footer_nav             → snippet name that renders the vertical's footer nav
    head_snippet           → snippet name rendered before </head> for vertical assets
    hide_blank_feature_media → 'true' if SP Features should drop empty media slots
    hero_fallback_tokens   → comma list of image-url tokens that trigger the
                             hero fallback image (placeholder art detection)
    hero_fallback_image    → asset filename used as the hero fallback image

  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ADDING A NEW PACK / VERTICAL
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  1. Add a new `when '<suffix>'` branch below.
  2. Fill in the fields the vertical needs (omit any it doesn't).
  3. Create templates/*.<suffix>.json for content composition only.
  4. Do NOT edit core sections, layout, or cart files — they read this registry.

  Verticals that only need preset CSS + content (skincare, electronics, etc.)
  load their styling through templates/*.<suffix>.json custom-liquid and do not
  need a branch here unless they require identity overrides.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign sp_reg_vertical = vertical
  if sp_reg_vertical == blank
    assign sp_reg_vertical = template.suffix
  endif

  case sp_reg_vertical
    when 'supplement'
      case field
        when 'active'
          echo 'supplement'
        when 'html_class'
          echo 'sp-vertical-visual-neutral sp-supplement'
        when 'brand_name'
          echo 'Daily Vitality'
        when 'product_handle'
          echo 'daily-vitality-complex'
        when 'title_index'
          echo 'Daily Vitality — Daily Wellness, Simplified'
        when 'title_cart'
          echo 'Your Cart | Daily Vitality'
        when 'title_product_suffix'
          echo ' | Daily Vitality'
        when 'footer_hidden_links'
          echo 'energy,daily vitality'
        when 'footer_nav'
          echo 'sp-vertical-footer-nav'
        when 'head_snippet'
          echo 'sp-supplement-head'
        when 'hide_blank_feature_media'
          echo 'true'
        when 'hero_fallback_tokens'
          echo 'snowboard,gift-card,ski-wax,Main_b13ad453'
        when 'hero_fallback_image'
          echo 'sp-supplement-daily-vitality-product.svg'
      endcase
  endcase
-%}
